==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Theosophist
<hw>The*os"o*phist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One addicted to
theosophy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>theosophist</qex> is one who gives you a theory of God,
or of the works of God, which has not reason, but an inspiration of his
own, for its basis.</q> <rj><qau>R. A. Vaughan.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Theosophistical</ent>⟦br⟧
